<br>
The way that dual wield in DAoC works is that EITHER hand can go off on a normal swing and there is a % chance that both will swing. Now, it is the first part that makes the change here. In EQ you put your best weapon in the primary because the secondary only works on a successful dual roll. In DAoC, either hand can swing, so it is best to have the same weapon in each hand, or at least weapons with similar delays.<br>
<br>
